A former President of the Nigerian Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki has faulted the ban placed on Twitter operations in Nigeria. Saraki said the ban should not be the response from the Nigerian President,Muhammadu Buhari. Read Saraki: “No sir! This should not be the response from the president of a nation with a vibrant youthful population for whom #Twitter is part of their daily lives and a source of their income and livelihood. This must be reviewed.” Minister of Infirmation, Alhaji Lai Mohammed had announced the ban in a statement released by Segun Adeyemi, Special Assistant (Media) in the office of the President. The decision has attracted an avalanche of reactions from Nigerians. Link: https://twitter.com/bukolasaraki/status/1400864502330101763?s=24 The United States of America ambassador to Nigeria, James Entwistle, yesterday assured the president of the Senate, Dr Bukola Saraki, of his country’s continued support for Nigeria’s fight against Boko Haram. The envoy gave this assurance when he paid a courtesy visit on the Senate resident yesterday. Entwistle informed Saraki… In "News" ...Gives Him Upto June 12 to Resign Over Offa Bank Robbery    ...Vows to Occupy NASS if He Refuses to Quit    By Chibuike Nwabuko   Abuja (Sundiata Post)  - A group under the auspices of Coalition of Civil Society for Good Governance and Democracy (CCSGGD) has accused the Senate… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Senate President Dr. Bukola Saraki on Sunday called on the Government of Qatar to end its visa restriction on Nigerians. According to a statement by his Media Office, Saraki made the request at a meeting with the Prime Minister and Minister of Interior… In "Top Stories"